OspfOperStatus.name: OspfOperStatus
OspfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of an OSPF Protocol Manager entity.

wwpLeosOspfRFC1583Comp.name: wwpLeosOspfRFC1583Comp
wwpLeosOspfRFC1583Comp.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 16.4.1 External path preferences
wwpLeosOspfRFC1583Comp.description: Indicates metrics used to choose among multiple AS-external-LSAs. When RFC1583Compatibility is set to TRUE, only cost will be used when choosing among multiple AS-external-LSAs advertising the same destination. When RFC1583Compatibility is set to FALSE, preference will be driven first by type of path using cost only to break ties. In order to minimize the chance of routing loops, all OSPF routers in an OSPF routing domain should have RFC1583Compatibility set identically. When there are routers present that have not been updated with the functionality specified in RFC2328 Section 16.4.1, all routers should have RFC1583Compatibility set to TRUE. Otherwise, all routers should have RFC1583Compatibility set to FALSE, preventing all routing loops.

wwpLeosOspfOperStatus.name: wwpLeosOspfOperStatus
wwpLeosOspfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of OSPF.

wwpLeosOspfOpaqueLsaSupport.name: wwpLeosOspfOpaqueLsaSupport
wwpLeosOspfOpaqueLsaSupport.description: The router's support for Opaque LSA types. This value cannot be changed when OSPF is active and operStatus is up.

wwpLeosOspfTrafficEngSupport.name: wwpLeosOspfTrafficEngSupport
wwpLeosOspfTrafficEngSupport.description: The router's support for OSPF traffic engineering.

wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCount.description: The number of type-11 LSAs in the external database.

wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfExtOpLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all type-11 LSAs in the external Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfNumUpdPending.name: wwpLeosOspfNumUpdPending
wwpLeosOspfNumUpdPending.description: The number of updates that are pending addition to the Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfNumUpdMerged.name: wwpLeosOspfNumUpdMerged
wwpLeosOspfNumUpdMerged.description: The number of updates that have been merged into the Link State Database since the last routing calculation.

wwpLeosOspfNumCksumsPending.name: wwpLeosOspfNumCksumsPending
wwpLeosOspfNumCksumsPending.description: The number of LSAs in the Link State Database which are now due to have their checksum checked.

wwpLeosOspfCalcMaxDelay.name: wwpLeosOspfCalcMaxDelay
wwpLeosOspfCalcMaxDelay.description: The maximum delay before the Routing Table is recalculated following a change to the Link State Database. (Recalculation is delayed to reduce the frequency of recalculations of the Routing Table). This parameter has units of milliseconds. A value of 0 indicates that a routing calculation will immediately follow an update to the database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaTable.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaTable
wwpLeosOspfAreaTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Section 6 The Area Data Struc- ture
wwpLeosOspfAreaTable.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of the router's attached areas.

wwpLeosOspfAreaEntry.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaEntry
wwpLeosOspfAreaEntry.description: Information describing the configured parame- ters and cumulative statistics of one of the router's attached areas.

wwpLeosOspfAreaId.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaId
wwpLeosOspfAreaId.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.2 Area parameters
wwpLeosOspfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying an area. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

wwpLeosOspfAreaTransitCapability.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaTransitCapability
wwpLeosOspfAreaTransitCapability.description: This parameter indicates whether the area can carry data traffic that neither originates nor terminates in the area itself. This parameter is calculated when the area's shortest-path tree is built.

wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-1 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaRtrLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-1 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-2 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaNetLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-2 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-3 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaSummLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-3 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-4 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaSummAsLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-4 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-7 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaNssaLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-7 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCount.description: The number of LSAs with LS type-10 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfAreaOpLsaCksumSum.description: The 32 bit sum of LS checksums of all LSAs with LS type-10 in this area's Link State Database.

wwpLeosOspfIfTable.name: wwpLeosOspfIfTable
wwpLeosOspfIfTable.reference: OSPF Version 2, Appendix C.3 Router interface parameters
wwpLeosOspfIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the inter- faces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

wwpLeosOspfIfEntry.name: wwpLeosOspfIfEntry
wwpLeosOspfIfEntry.description: The OSPF Interface Entry describes one inter- face from the viewpoint of OSPF.

wwpLeosOspfIfIpAddress.name: wwpLeosOspfIfIpAddress
wwpLeosOspfIfIpAddress.description: The IP address of this OSPF interface.

wwpLeosOspfAddressLessIf.name: wwpLeosOspfAddressLessIf
wwpLeosOspfAddressLessIf.description: For the purpose of easing the instancing of addressed and addressless interfaces; This variable takes the value 0 on interfaces with IP Addresses, and the corresponding value of ifIndex for interfaces having no IP Address.

wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCount.name: wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCount
wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCount.description: The total number of link-local link state advertisements in this interface's link-local link state database.

wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCksumSum.name: wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCksumSum
wwpLeosOspfIfLsaCksumSum.description: The 32-bit unsigned sum of the link-state advertisements' LS checksums contained in this interface's link-local link state database. The sum can be used to determine if there has been a change in the interface's link state database, and to compare the interface link-state database of routers attached to the same subnet.

wwpLeosOspfIfOperStatus.name: wwpLeosOspfIfOperStatus
wwpLeosOspfIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of this interface.

wwpLeosOspfIfNetMask.name: wwpLeosOspfIfNetMask
wwpLeosOspfIfNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this entry. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the hosts bits set to 0.

wwpLeosOspfIfTransmitTimerDelay.name: wwpLeosOspfIfTransmitTimerDelay
wwpLeosOspfIfTransmitTimerDelay.description: The time this interface will delay a LSU packet, in order to add more LSAs to the packet before sending. Setting this correctly can reduce the network traffic. This is configurable on a per-interface basis.
